    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We are not following ERC-1822 strictly, but the change we made is compatible in the sense that the return value of `proxiableUUID` is equal to the slot being used. This means that an ERC-1822 contract would not be confused about whether an implementation is compatible with itself, when inspecting the value of `proxiableUUID`. We had the intention to propose this as a change to ERC-1822.\r\n\r\nWe see value in using the storage slot defined in ERC-1967 for this purpose.",
